<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Approves Health Act Amendments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Approves Health Act Amendments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2701172894 Sofia BTA in English 1515 GMT 27 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2701172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Sofia, January 27 (BTA) -- Today the Council of 
Ministers approved a bill amending and supplementing the Public 
Health Act under which the owners of medical care establishments 
would not be allowed to work for state or municipal medical care 
establishments at the same time. It is envisaged to grant the 
medical care establishments independent juristic persons status 
which, according to Minister of Health Tancho Gugalov, will make 
it possible for them to negotiate the required funds with the 
municipalities. The fines for not complying with the standards 
of sanitation and hygiene would be increased, varying from 1,000 
to 1.5 million leva. The Public Health Act operating now was 
adopted in 1973. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

