<H3> <TI>   Minister Says Health Care at `Brink of Collapse' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Says Health Care at `Brink of Collapse' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304122194 Prague CTK in English 0726 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1304122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bratislava, April 12 (CTK) -- [Passage omitted] 
The funding of health care has brought it to the brink of 
collapse with a 2 billion crown debt ($60 million). Due to 
this, urgent measures must be taken to prevent the system from 
collapsing, Health Minister Tibor Sagat tells the independent 
NARODNA OBRODA. 
  First of all, supplies of medicaments cannot be halted, says 
Sagat. The government has provided the National Insurance Fund 
with a half-a-billion crown "injection," while additional money 
is expected by the end of April, he adds. 
  Moravcik's cabinet will try again to settle last year's debt 
of the health facilities. However, previous techniques of 
comprehensive repayment only demoralized the management, Sagat 
says. That is why it is necessary to apply a differentiating 
approach regarding repayment of debts, while Sagat himself he is 
about to establish the criteria in person in cooperation with 
the Association of Hospitals, he adds. 

</TEXT>

