    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on epidemics and diseases monitored through 3 March. 
<H5>  Brazil </H5>
  Leptospirosis -- The summer rains have caused a 
leptospirosis 
outbreak which has already killed three people in Sao Paulo 
State, where 78 cases had been registered as of 25 February. 
(Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 26 Feb 94 p 6) 
  Meningitis -- The Ceara Health Secretariat has reported that 
a type-B meningitis outbreak has killed seven people in 
Fortaleza and Sobral, where 45 cases were registered in 45 days. 
(Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 26 Feb 94 p 6) 
  AIDS -- Health authorities from Sao Jose do Rio Preto, 451 
km 
from Sao Paulo, are concerned because this city of 290,000 
inhabitants has the third highest rate of AIDS in the country 
after Santos and Sao Paulo. According to the regional health 
office, every day an average of over one person contracts the 
HIV virus. (Rio de Janeiro JORNAL DO BRASIL in Portuguese 2 Mar 
94 p 12) 

</TEXT>

