<F P=106> [Report by Eli Bohadna] </F>
  [Text] Over the past few years, 12 employees of the 
Nuclear Research Center in Dimona developed cancer and three of 
them died. 
  The families of 10 employees who got cancer have appealed to 
the courts to order the center's management to divulge all the 
material required to investigate the circumstances leading to 
the illness. 
  The Atomic Energy Commission claims that the incidence of 
cancer among reactor employees is no higher than among the 
population at large. 

