  In order to provide a wider range of information about AIDS 
and HIV in the United Kingdom, the Communicable Disease Report 
has recently introduced a new schedule for publication of 
surveillance data. This is designed to focus on different 
aspects of the data throughout the year. So that a wider 
audience can also benefit from this improved presentation, the 
monthly and quarterly routine Press Notices will in future be 
replaced by new quarterly formats. These will provide 
considerable additional information over that presented 
formerly. This is the last in the current series of Monthly and 
Quarterly AIDS and IV figures. The new format will begin in 
April. [passage on editorial notes omitted] 
