<H3> <TI>   Total of 1,321 HIV Cases Reported Nationwide </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Total of 1,321 HIV Cases Reported Nationwide </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0804100294 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0804100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Professor Le Dien Hong, deputy chairman of the 
National Committee for Preventing HIV/AIDS, reported that during 
the first three months of 1994, a total of 197 HIV cases were 
discovered. During the same period, 46 were admitted as AIDS 
patients and 14 died. 
  Thus far, the number of HIV cases in Vietnam has reached 
1,321, among them 1,242 Vietnamese in 29 provinces and 
municipalities. Professor Le Dien Hong said, however, that the 
number of HIV infected persons in Vietnam is dramatically higher 
than the number made public. This is because we have not 
conducted surveys on certain groups of people such as 
prostitutes and drug addicts who are vulnerable to HIV. 

</TEXT>

