  [Text] Patna, Feb. 18 -- AIDS is threatening to assume a 
menacing proportion in Bihar with 61 HIV positive cases being 
recorded till last December. Out of the 61 HIV positive cases, 
13 have been declared full blown cases of AIDS after the Western 
Blot test. 
  A senior official of the health department, preparing 
anonymity, said the maximum number of Elisa as well as Western 
Blot positive cases have been reported from Patna where 41 HIV 
and eight Western Blot positive cases had been detected so far. 

</TEXT>

