<H3> <TI>   Moscow Ambulance Workers Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Ambulance Workers Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Violation of Labor Law Alleged </H4>

<F P=102> 94WE0207B Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 27 Jan 94 p 
2 </F>

<F P=103> 94WE0207B </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed untitled article datelined Moscow under the </F>
"In Brief" rubric] 
  [Text] The capital's Ambulance Service has decided to 
strike. February 14 has been designated the day on which the 
strike will begin. The council of the service's labor collective 
made the respective announcement. It was noted in the 
announcement that on 25 January 1994 Anatoliy Solovyev, head of 
Moscow's Main Medical Administration, signed an order regarding 
reorganization of the Ambulance Service station. The 
announcement stated that this was done without the consent of 
the service's personnel and in violation of the law "Regarding 
the Procedure for Resolving Collective Labor Disagreements 
(Conflicts)." In accordance with Article 7 of the said law, a 
conference of the labor collective held on 14 February 1994 will 
decide the matter of the form and date of the beginning of the 
strike of the No. 03 Service in Moscow. 

</TEXT>

