<F P=106> [Article signed TP: "Security Policy -- European </F>
Cooperation: 200 Scientists Meet in Zurich"] 
  [Text] A total of 200 European scientists and experts are 
meeting in Zurich until Thursday [28 April] to promote 
scientific cooperation in matters of security policy. An 
information exchange association is expected to be set up. The 
organizers of the meeting are the Federal Military Department 
and the Federal Department for Foreign Affairs. 
  The objective of this international conference is to promote 
the creation of research institutes with democratic objectives 
in Central and Eastern Europe. 
  The research institute on security policy matters and on 
analyzing conflicts of Zurich's Federal Polytechnic School and 
the UN Research Institute on Disarmament are participating in 
this conference as are approximately 100 research institutes on 
security policy issues. 
  Despite tight budgets, international cooperation is 
essential, Federal Counselor Kaspar Villiger said at the opening 
of the conference. International criminal organizations, 
uncontrolled migration flows, rising numbers of mass destruction 
weapons, and increased nationalist feelings are all serious 
problems for security policy, he added. 

</TEXT>

