<H3> <TI>   Government Confirms Bundeswehr Stores Radioactive Material </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Confirms Bundeswehr Stores Radioactive Material </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2503133894 Hamburg DPA in German 1243 GMT 25 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2503133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Radioactive material is being stored 
at Bundeswehr facilities in Storkow near Berlin. In its 
response to a request from the Party of Democratic 
Socialism/Left Ticket, the Federal Press Office has stated that 
this is confirmed by the Federal Government. The facilities 
were taken over from the National People's Army of the GDR, and 
most of the radioactive material has come from those stocks. "A 
considerable part" of the material was also stored there by the 
GDR Ministry for State Security. The material consists of 
"sealed radioactive sources," mainly of the Cobalt 60 
radionuclide. The Bundeswehr was looking for ways of using this 
material, it was stated. 

</TEXT>

