<H3> <TI>     EU Concerned About Nuclear Import From East Europe, Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Concerned About Nuclear Import From East Europe, Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1904150294 London REUTER Textline Database in English 14 
Apr 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1904150294 </F>
<F P=104>  London REUTER Textline Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article from Brussels EUROPE: "EU: Commission </F>
Prepares Communication on Clandestine Imports of Nuclear 
Material From East"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 13 Apr 94 (AGENCE EUROPE) - The Council of 
the European Union gave the following response to written 
question No. E-3697/93 by Mr. A. Smith: "The Council does not 
have information on contraband trade in nuclear material, but it 
shares the concerns of the honourable member of the European 
Parliament regarding the consequences of fraudulent traffic into 
the European Union of nuclear and/or radioactive material from 
the Central and Eastern European countries and the former Soviet 
Union. In this context, the Commission is currently preparing a 
communication to the Council which should make it possible to 
get a better idea of the scope of this problem as well as action 
which could be taken at Community level in terms of information. 

</TEXT>

