<H3> <TI>     Bonn Provides DM3.5 Million To Scrap Russian Warheads </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bonn Provides DM3.5 Million To Scrap Russian Warheads </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1904191794 Hamburg DPA in German 1543 GMT 19 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1904191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The Federal Government will provide 
3.5 million German marks for the scrapping, dismantling, or 
conversion of Russian nuclear arms. This was stated by the 
Foreign Ministry in Bonn on Tuesday [19 April]. 
After a round of German-Russian talks, agreement was reached on, 
among other things, technical assistance, including special 
instruments and the safe dismantling of nuclear arms and their 
warheads. The Foreign Ministry further stated that a study on 
the conversion of weapons-grade plutonium would be initiated. 
In addition, cooperation for the destruction of chemical 
weapons will continue. 

</TEXT>

