<H3> <TI>   Minister Says Government Not To Slow Down Missile Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Says Government Not To Slow Down Missile Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0904085294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0904085294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The minister of state for defense, Mr. Mallikarjun, 
has asserted that India will not succumb to pressure from any 
country to slow down its missile development program. Talking 
to newsmen in Madras today, he said that Prithvi 
[surface-to-surface missile] has been successfully tested and it 
is for the technical experts to decide about its induction into 
the armed forces. 
  Mr. Mallikarjun also expressed concern over the possibility 
of a military imbalance in the region if Washington supplies 
F-16 jets to Pakistan. 

</TEXT>

