<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspodent Mikhail Karlov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 6 TASS -- Kazakhstan palnnes to build 
its second fast-neutron reactor. It will have the capacity of 
170 megawatt. The newspaper of the Kazakh business circles 
PANORAMA road the decision was taken on the strength of the 
results of the operation in Kazakhstan foir other 20 years of 
the worlds first BM-350 fast-neutron reactor, the only one in 
the CIS that is situated not far form the city of Shevchenko. 
[sentence as received] 
  ITAR-TASS learned form Rossenergoatom concern, Russian 
nuclear energy concern, that this statement is not keeping with 
reality. A more powerful reactor, BM-600, that is regarded as 
the most reliable and most safest has long been functioning at 
the Beloyarsk nuclear power station. The project for the 
instolation at the same station of a reactor of the next 
generation of BM-800, has actually been completed. A similar 
reactor is to be assembled in the Chelyabinsk area. 
  The construction of a new nuclear power palnt in Kazakhstan 
is a state project. Funds in the amount of 15 million tenge 
have already been allocated. But the problem of design work 
thaqt is done mostly by Russian and Kazakh specialists has not 
yet been resolved. 

